%N A394299 a(n) is the numerator of the expected absolute difference of two primes p1, p2 drawn randomly from the interval 2^n <= p < 2^(n+1) without replacement.
%e A394299 1/1, 2/1, 2/1, 38/5, 236/21, 850/39, 1000/23, 26840/301, 477368/2775, 47036/137, ...
%e A394299 a(4)/A394300(4) = 38/5: The 5 primes in the interval [16,31] are 17, 19, 23, 29, 31. Their A036378(4)*(A036378(4)-1)/2 = (5*4)/2 = 10 mutual differences are 2, 6, 12, 14, 4, 10, 12, 6, 8, 2, with sum 76.
%e A394299 If all numbers from the interval were in the urn, there would be A006516(4) = 120 pairs, with a mean of A000051(4)/3 = (2^4 + 1)/3 = 17/3. The following table shows that the naive assumption that the expected value of the differences of the drawn prime number pairs is always larger than that obtained when all numbers are in the urn is incorrect.
%e A394299 .
